And if  only two events can be true at once in a problem use this equation P(A ∩ B ∩ NOTC) + P(A ∩ NOTB ∩ C) + P(NOTA ∩ B ∩ C)?

P(only second event) = P(A∩B) + P(A∩C) + P(B∩C) − 3×P(A∩B∩C)
P(only third event) = P(A∩B∩C)
P(all events) = P(A∩B∩C)


P(A or B) = P(A) + P(B) − P(A and B) 
P(A and B) = -P(A or B) + P(A) + P(B)

